rComments: She uses Respondus which I find very disrespectful, controlling, and defies the whole purpose of the learning process!

She has an amazing personality but thats about it Literally no content on her brightspace Uses respondus for tests Never responded to any of my emails tbh Doesnt record anything so if ur not 100% in class taking notes you wont know what is going on

Omg horrible. Uses respondus for the tests and exam and doesn't let us use a dictionary. doesn't record any of the classes and over explains everything to the point where you don't understand anything else. posts activities on brightspace but with no corrections. goes over tests in class but with no correction. would never take her again!

She is probably the sweetest FLS prof that Ive had. Shes very kind and never makes you feel bad if you are struggling to speak and will try to help you in a non-condescending way. She heavily relies on the textbook and class participation in her lectures
She's nice as a person, but very boring and not engaging as a professor. She is very monotone and kind of hard to listen to for a long period of time.

N'est pas bonne. Ce cours contient la grammaire et la rédaction d'un rapport de recommandations. Elle n'aide pas les élèves pour leur rapport et elle est très vague lors de ses explications. De plus, elle ne corrige pas bien le rapport. Cependant, elle explique bien la grammaire .
She is very nice, gives lots of practice questions for the lecture material and is easily approachable.

Prof Sefrioui is great! Her classes are fun. She delivers very clearly the material. She knows her stuff! Very very knowledgeable. You have to study though if you want to have a good mark. Don't miss lectures.

I changed sections because I was told that she was a better prof. I thought she was pretty good. I do not regret it. What I honestly like about her is that she is always willing to help. We had a group project, and we were able to meet with her often to discuss it. She actually wanted us to go and see her when we can to talk about our report :)
Very boring class. I would not take again, the exams were extremely hard.

Its an easy class if french is your first language. Otherwise you will have to work for it a bit. Shes a great prof and cares a lot. From what Ive seen almost everyone gets around 70-75 on the group project. Make sure to study her notes.

Pretty good prof, but she obviously wasn't interested in the class she was teaching (to be fair, none of the students were, either). Tests aren't particularly tough but my grade got brought down quite a bit by the group project, which isn't very clearly explained or guided.

First midterm was a struggle (know your stuff and do lots of examples) while the second was a lot easier. I had an 89 before the group project (which brought my grade down drastically) done with little guidance and unclear objectives. Attendance is taken when she remembers. Lectures are fairly interesting; I really liked her personality.

She is a tough grader. Her expectations are very unclear. She doesn't seem to care about the class she was teaching. This class was supposed to help with my bio class but it wasn't helpful at all. Her assignments had nothing to do with what we were learning in class. The class was always behind in going over the material we learned in bio.

If you aren't francophone, avoid this professor!! I took an FLS course which was supposed to help in BIO1530, but was absolutely useless! She's a very tough marker and she isn't very interesting. The assignments were also super random and did not help at all. This class was supposed to help my GPA, not bring it down. My least favourite prof.

Honestly, I was very sceptical to take a 3 hour lecture on a Monday night, especially a French course. But I didn't regret it! She is very passionate. She made the course pleasant and easy to follow. And she was always available to meet with me and answer my questions outside of the class. Surprisingly I enjoyed the class :)

The class didn't properly follow the course outline given by the school. No medical terminology was ever used. The expectations for the group project were not clear. She takes attendance on random days so you have to make sure to go to class, it counts in your final grade.
If you can avoid her, do so. Most boring, pointless course I have ever taken! Save yourself while you still can.

Prof superbe! Je la recommande fortement pour un cours de Français. Elle explique clairement les idées, et elle est toujours disponible pour rencontrer les élèves après le cours pour des questions. Elle ma vraiment aidée pour ma transition du secondaire à luniversité.  Je ne suis pas forte en français, mais jai beaucoup appris :)

Elle n'est pas très claire dans ce qu'elle s'attend de recevoir. Ce cours comprend 2 examens mi-sessions(grammaire), un rapport de groupe et l'examen final. Elle répond aux questions de façon brève et n'aide pas à améliorer la compréhension de l'étudiant. Rarement disponible après les heures de classes. Elle connais la matière, toujours à l'heure..

She's young and  smart, always very well prepared for her classes and very easy to approach. Let's face it.... French classes are bored! But she makes sure hers is not. Attendance is mandatory and there is an important group project. If you attend and pay attention in class, you'll get a good grade.
Elle contredit le livre qu'elle recommande a multiple reprise. De plus, la possibilité d'obtenir une note élevé est mince du a la subjectivité présente dans sa correction.

Je voudrais dire qu'elle est une enseignante-universitaire sympa, jolie et approchable. Elle est très agréable, toujours à l'heure et bien preparé pour ses classes. MAIS, elle note les examens, fiches de lecture et compte-rendu très difficile. Elle vous traite comme un(e) francophone alors soyez-prête.  En générale, elle est très enseigné.
Nice prof.
Nice. hope to get to know her better.
Great prof, still new when I took the course but overall not bad!

Personnellement  j'ai adoré son cours.  Elle a une façon simple d'expliquer les choses. Moi qui suis timide, j'ai eu aucun problème à l'approcher et lui poser mes questions. En plus, elle est toujours de bonne humeur :)

Elle est jeune, sympa, drôle par moment. Elle explique clairement et simplement le cours. Ses exams reflètent le contenu de son cours. Elle est toujours prête à rencontrer ses étudiants pour les aider. Je la recommande.
Good prof, very helpful. She's always available to help.
Great prof!

Le cours est bien structuré et très clair.  Elle sait définitivement de quoi elle parle. Pour le gros travail de fin de session, toutes les étapes sont abordées en classe en détails. On sait vraiment ce qu'elle veut. En plus, elle est toujours disponible si on a des questions.
Really confusing unstructured class. Wouldn't explain 20 page assignement or answer questions about it until a week before it was due, then throughout that week kept contradicting herself.
tough grader
Horrendous. If you're going to tell us to BUY a book then you should NOT tell us NOT to follow the BOOK. Jeezus christ. Worst prof, grader.
WORST PROFESSOR, DOESNT FOLLOW THE BOOK , HARDEST GRADER ON WORLD HISTORY, TO AVOID AT ALL COST

Horrible. She goes against the book that she recommended herself and her tests are absolutely horrible. Every other class is multiple choice but us no! she says one thing for 2 minutes in class on an exact day and puts a question in the test to "see if you were listening" at that exact moment. like please..you're boring, obviously I'm not listening
